    "body": "In the event it assists anyone:\r\n[starship.bash.patch](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/16451727/starship_bash.patch.txt)\r\n\r\nThe above follows from @ghostbuster91's suggestion to hard-code in some semantic prompt capabilities to a shell's init (bash, in this case), to test how they might function if someone did invest the time to add the required hooks.\r\n\r\nI tried all of the semantic shell functionality I could with KDE's Konsole, as well as Starship features I typically use, and everything appeared to work (including mouse cursor positioning, and Starship's timer functionality). That said, there are plenty of Starship features I'm yet to try, and I haven't reached for other terminal emulators and tools — or looked at how this could be implemented for other shells.\r\n\r\nI'm not much of a rustacean, but can help test features or perhaps look at a partial implementation down the line.",
